parameters: This event makes use of two new plugins that I downloaded.
I was having some issue getting an animation to play on
the chest, it just kept happening in the middle of the
screen no matter what source I gave it. So I downloaded
a plugin that allows us to play animations directly on
top of an event or specific coordinates.
I chose to use coordinates because it allowed me to use
the same spell animation in multiple places without
needing to create two versions of the animation.
(This is probably how I'll do animations in the future
if/when we need them)
This event also uses an awesome plugin that allows us
to change which party member the "Set Movement Route"
event points towards, so we can have our followers
actually do things instead of just Leucre.
These two plugin commands below tell all followers
to stop chasing the main player, which allows us to
manipulate their position because they are no longer
locked to the follower.
Follower 0 is the party leader, so Follower 1 is
Miana.
Follower StopChase
Follower 1
Since we've changed the focus to Follower 1, the game
thinks that "Player" is the second member of the party
so "Set Movement Route" is now controlling Miana and
not Leucre
\pop[-1]Leucre: What is a chest doing over on a

\pop[-1]Leucre: Me too... Hey! You know how to use

We still have follower 1 (Miana) as the focus, so we can
even use balloon icons to appear over different followers
heads.
\pop[-2]Miana: Leucre... That would be a gross
misuse of my abilities, but I guess it's either
that or continue not knowing... Alright, here goes

The next two lines declare the inital location on the
map that the Flash animation will play.
This uses the Flash<4,v44,v45> spell animation.
v44 and v45 are both of the map X and Y coordinates
I manually set in the previous lines.
Here I'm setting the coordinates to where I want the
next flash to happen, which is where the chest is
"teleporting" to.
The next few lines are me switching between which
party member the "Set Movement Route" command is focusing
on to allow both Leucre and Miana to face a certain
direction for the sake of the scene.
